{
  "text": "Unmeasured confounding is another limitation. Although we adjusted for five confounders, it is possible that other patient factors influenced outcomes. For example, a US study was assessed the relationship between self-reported disease burden and functional improvement during and after inpatient rehabilitation [CITATION_1] . Compared with patients without chronic conditions, those who had a stroke had significantly worse self-care, transfer and locomotion ratings.",
